Reverse Polish Notation Calculator
==================================

   The first example is that of a simple double-precision @{i}reverse polish
notation@{ui} calculator (a calculator using postfix operators).  This
example provides a good starting point, since operator precedence is
not an issue.  The second example will illustrate how operator
precedence is handled.

   The source code for this calculator is named @{b}rpcalc.y@{ub}.  The @{b}.y@{ub}
extension is a convention used for Bison input files.


 @{" Decls " Link "Rpcalc Decls"}                Bison and C declarations for rpcalc.
 @{" Rules " Link "Rpcalc Rules"}                Grammar Rules for rpcalc, with explanation.
