Outline of a Bison Grammar
==========================

   A Bison grammar file has four main sections, shown here with the
appropriate delimiters:

     %{
     @{i}C declarations@{ui}
     %}
     
     @{i}Bison declarations@{ui}
     
     %%
     @{i}Grammar rules@{ui}
     %%
     
     @{i}Additional C code@{ui}

   Comments enclosed in @{b}/* ... */@{ub} may appear in any of the sections.


 @{" C Declarations " Link "C Declarations"}     Syntax and usage of the C declarations section.
 @{" Bison Declarations " Link "Bison Declarations"}   Syntax and usage of the Bison declarations section.
 @{" Grammar Rules " Link "Grammar Rules"}      Syntax and usage of the grammar rules section.
 @{" C Code " Link "C Code"}             Syntax and usage of the additional C code section.


@EndNode

