Invoking Bison
**************

   The usual way to invoke Bison is as follows:

     bison @{i}infile@{ui}

   Here @{i}infile@{ui} is the grammar file name, which usually ends in @{b}.y@{ub}.  The
parser file's name is made by replacing the @{b}.y@{ub} with @{b}.tab.c@{ub}.  Thus, the
@{b}bison foo.y@{ub} filename yields @{b}foo.tab.c@{ub}, and the @{b}bison hack/foo.y@{ub}
filename yields @{b}hack/foo.tab.c@{ub}.


 @{" Bison Options " Link "Bison Options"}      All the options described in detail,
			in alphabetical order by short options.
 @{" Option Cross Key " Link "Option Cross Key"}   Alphabetical list of long options.
 @{" VMS Invocation " Link "VMS Invocation"}     Bison command syntax on VMS.


@EndNode

@Node "Bison Options" "Bison.guide/Bison Options"
@Next "Option Cross Key"
